{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01BBGDLhw6ThNRwB19Pifeou","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I can see the Elasticsearch StatefulSet doesn't have `keystore.secureSettings` configured. To securely pass credentials to Elasticsearch without putting them in `elasticsearch.yml` or env vars, I need to use the Elasticsearch keystore.\n\nThe approach is:\n1. Get the MinIO credentials from the `minio-root` secret\n2. Create the `es-secure-settings` secret with the S3 plugin settings\n3. Configure the StatefulSet to mount this secret as a keystore using the `keystore.secureSettings` volume\n4. The Elasticsearch pods need to pick up the keystore settings\n5. Register the snapshot repository with those credentials\n6. Create a snapshot\n\nI'm realizing that Elasticsearch 8.11.1 requires the `repository-s3` plugin to work with S3-compatible storage like MinIO, and I need to verify whether it's included in the standard Docker image or if it needs to be installed separately.\n\nLet me check if the S3 plugin is already installed in the running pods and review the MinIO credentials and Elasticsearch configuration to understand the current setup.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1824,"cache_read_input_tokens":29053,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1824},"output_tokens":24,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"21b7b920-abe4-4cd7-9ab0-ac50f77ea4d3","uuid":"6e9ec4ca-acd9-461c-824a-8c261eefa0f7","request_id":"req_011CcfEhDGB6PsBx37Q7t1dA"}
