{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Pq82jZSJBU5HnAGPkAQm6u","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can see that the `keystore` subPath volumeMount is at index 0. I need to:\n1. Remove it (op: remove at index 0)\n2. Add command and args to copy the keystore and start ES\n\nLet me use a JSON patch to:\n1. Remove the keystore subPath mount from main container (index 0)\n2. Add command to the main container\n3. Add args to the main container\n\nAlso, I need to update the init container to properly handle the keystore path. Looking at the init container setup - it should already be working (creating keystore in /keystore/). The issue was just the subPath mount in the main container.\nSo my strategy is to have the main container copy the keystore file from `/keystore/` to the expected location in the Elasticsearch config directory on startup, then proceed with the normal entrypoint. I'll construct a JSON patch that removes the problematic volumeMount and adds a bash command with arguments to handle the copy operation.\n\nBut I realize I still need the keystore volume to be accessible to the main container so it can read from it during startup. I'll add back a volumeMount for the keystore emptyDir, this time without the subPath restriction, so the container can access the files it needs.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4446,"cache_read_input_tokens":53072,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4446},"output_tokens":37,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"21b7b920-abe4-4cd7-9ab0-ac50f77ea4d3","uuid":"b072a0b7-d05c-497f-bc1f-99c6921fa133","request_id":"req_011CcfFX9tcadmJh2BrnM2Rx"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Pq82jZSJBU5HnAGPkAQm6u","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01H9n8Qk1XfHjM9chbEGFVkA","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"kubectl patch statefulset es -n elasticsearch --type=json -p '[\n  {\"op\": \"remove\", \"path\": \"/spec/template/spec/containers/0/volumeMounts/0\"},\n  {\"op\": \"add\", \"path\": \"/spec/template/spec/containers/0/volumeMounts/-\", \"value\": {\"name\": \"keystore\", \"mountPath\": \"/keystore-stage\", \"readOnly\": true}},\n  {\"op\": \"add\", \"path\": \"/spec/template/spec/containers/0/command\", \"value\": [\"/bin/bash\", \"-c\"]},\n  {\"op\": \"add\", \"path\": \"/spec/template/spec/containers/0/args\", \"value\": [\"cp /keystore-stage/elasticsearch.keystore /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/elasticsearch.keystore && chmod 600 /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/elasticsearch.keystore && exec /usr/local/bin/docker-entrypoint.sh eswrapper\"]}\n]' 2>&1","description":"Fix StatefulSet: remove bad subPath mount, add copy-then-start command"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4446,"cache_read_input_tokens":53072,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4446},"output_tokens":37,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"21b7b920-abe4-4cd7-9ab0-ac50f77ea4d3","uuid":"cc0b9ea8-da35-4fc5-b384-143aef0b0dcd","request_id":"req_011CcfFX9tcadmJh2BrnM2Rx"}
