{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_015ZZk5aQiuzBGGhUmZCyPkJ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Everything is confirmed working. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n**Root causes fixed:**\n1. **Missing MinIO service** — `minio-init` job had run before a `Service` for the MinIO pod existed, so the bucket was never created and ES couldn't reach MinIO. Created `service/minio` (port 9000) to expose the MinIO deployment.\n2. **Missing `es-backups` bucket** — Created it with a temporary `minio/mc` pod after the service was up.\n3. **No keystore credentials** — ES cannot authenticate to MinIO without `s3.client.default.access_key` / `secret_key` in the Elasticsearch keystore.\n\n**What was configured:**\n\n| Resource | Action |\n|---|---|\n| `Secret/es-secure-settings` | Created with `s3.client.default.access_key` and `s3.client.default.secret_key` (both `minioadmin`) |\n| `StatefulSet/es` | Added `setup-keystore` init container that reads the secret and runs `elasticsearch-keystore add` to populate `/keystore/elasticsearch.keystore`; main container copies it into the config dir at startup |\n| `Service/minio` | Created to expose port 9000 so Elasticsearch pods can resolve `minio.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local` |\n\n**Result:**\n- `minio-repo` repository registered (type `s3`, bucket `es-backups`, path-style access, HTTP protocol)\n- `snapshot-1` completed with **state: SUCCESS** — 1 shard, 0 failures, captured `test-index`"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":829,"cache_read_input_tokens":70050,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":829},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"21b7b920-abe4-4cd7-9ab0-ac50f77ea4d3","uuid":"5f778dfd-ae57-476d-a21c-122402e7de02","request_id":"req_011CcfG42agrETSCKNekK2mv"}
